+# Exploration 001 Report
+
+## Goal
+
+Freeze the smallest serious theorem-endpoint menu for `step-009`, using only
+local repository materials, and determine whether the live run-006
+pressure-Hessian branch has one exact theorem endpoint and contradiction line
+or only endpoint-adjacent bottleneck language.
+
+## Method
+
+- Read the step goal, controller decisions, run-006 planning artifacts, and
+  inherited obstruction notes named in the task prompt.
+- Distinguish theorem endpoints from proof architectures, bottleneck themes,
+  and packaging variants.
+- Record claims as `[VERIFIED]`, `[INFERRED]`, or `[PROPOSED]`.
+
+## Early Findings
+
+### Gate Imposed By The Step Goal And Decisions
+
+- [VERIFIED] `step-009/GOAL.md` requires one exact theorem endpoint, one
+  contradiction line, one literal cash-out, one progress currency, one minimum
+  threshold, and admission rules before any tensor packaging or observable
+  screening can count as progress.
+- [VERIFIED] `decision-013.md` invalidates the prior compactness-rigidity chain
+  because Step 1 failed to freeze one coherent framework-endpoint-temporal
+  ledger.
+- [VERIFIED] `decision-014.md` activates run `run-006` only on the stricter
+  condition that Step 1 first freeze one endpoint-complete ledger and kill the
+  branch immediately if that cannot be done concretely.
+
+## Open Questions
+
+- Which exact endpoint candidates remain serious after the run-006 selection?
+- Whether run-006 branch language names theorem endpoints or only proof
+  architectures/bottleneck themes.
+- Whether the inherited far-field pressure obstruction still fixes the most
+  concrete contradiction line.
+
+## Failed Attempts And Dead Ends
+
+- None yet.

