+# Exploration 001 Report
+
+## Goal
+
+Freeze the smallest serious theorem-endpoint menu for `step-009`, using only
+local repository materials, and determine whether the live run-006
+pressure-Hessian branch has one exact theorem endpoint and contradiction line
+or only endpoint-adjacent bottleneck language.
+
+## Method
+
+- Read the step goal, controller decisions, run-006 planning artifacts, and
+  inherited obstruction notes named in the task prompt.
+- Distinguish theorem endpoints from proof architectures, bottleneck themes,
+  and packaging variants.
+- Record claims as `[VERIFIED]`, `[INFERRED]`, or `[PROPOSED]`.
+
+## Early Findings
+
+### Gate Imposed By The Step Goal And Decisions
